svg.desc: Using a map of Germany, the chart shows the average annual nitrogen dioxide pollution measured at federal state and Federal Environment Agency air monitoring network points in 2016. The levels range from 3 to 82 micrograms per cubic metre.

div.div: NO₂ annual average value in micrograms per cubic metre (µg/m³)

div.p:
Source: Umweltbundesamt 2017.
